Plot:
Clint Eastwood stars as Walt Kowalski, a widower who holds 
onto his prejudices despite the changes in his Michigan 
neighborhood and the world around him. Kowalski is a grumpy, 
tough-minded, unhappy old man, who can't get along with 
either his kids or his neighbors, a Korean War veteran whose 
prize possession is a 1972 Gran Torino he keeps in mint 
condition. When his neighbor Tao, a young Hmong teenager 
under pressure from his gang member cousin, tries to steal 
his Gran Torino, Kowalski sets out to reform the youth. 
Drawn against his will into the life of Tao's family, 
Kowalski is soon taking steps to protect them from the 
gangs that infest their neighborhood.
